paper_metadata.title: MAIN TEXT
paper_metadata.extraction_summary: The paper discusses the role of protein misfolding in pregnancy, particularly in preeclampsia, and mentions the presence of aggregated proteoforms of transthyretin (TTR) in the serum of women with preeclampsia.

functional_data.summary: Aggregated proteoforms of TTR were detected in the serum of women with preeclampsia, suggesting a role in the pathogenesis of the condition.

variants.segregation_data: The presence of abnormal TTR aggregates is suggested to be causative of preeclampsia.
variants.additional_notes: The study indicates that TTR aggregates may contribute to the pathophysiology of preeclampsia.
key_quotes: Kalkunte et al. demonstrated the presence of aggregated proteoforms of transthyretin (TTR) in the serum of women with PE.

extraction_metadata.notes: Only one variant related to TTR was mentioned, with no specific cDNA or protein notation provided.
